jobs.description:
Working as a lawyer on the Westpac Global Derivatives Reform Project, a project dedicated to the implementation of various derivative reform rules and regulations, my role involves interpreting, implementing and advising on highly complex international and domestic laws and regulations in relation to OTC derivatives trading. This includes; 
o	Dodd Frank Title VII and CFTC Regulations (US); 
o	EMIR Regulations (Europe);  
o	Canadian Derivatives Transaction Reporting Rules (Canada); and 
o	ASIC Derivative Transaction Rules (Reporting) 2013 (Australia)

Providing statutory and strategic planning advice to a diverse variety of public and private sector clients on a number of projects including aged care, affordable housing, multi-dwelling residential, public recreational, mixed use and commercial projects. For these types of projects I independently provide the following:

- Feasibility reports addressing planning and infrastructure legislation, outlining strategic advice;
- Preparing Statement of Environmental Effects;
- Assist with the preparation of urban design reports including graphic presentation and visual representation of urban design principles (using Adobe Creative Suite). 
- Assist with the preparation of masterplans and strategic plans;
- Managing client expectations and council procedures;
- Managing reports, invoices and back of house operations;
- Coordination of marketing resources including monthly blog and newsletter (2016-2018);

This role involved coordinating and organising all social and sporting events associated with the UTS LSS; 
-	Portfolio of 3 Directors – Social Directors & Sport Director 
-	Managing an activities budget in excess of $100,000.00 per year; 
-	Collaborating with external businesses to secure sponsorship deals and negotiate business transactions;
-	Coordinating and designing the annual Law Ball with over 650 attendees held at Sydney Town hall; 
-	Coordinated UTS LSS Orientation Camp of 150 students; and 
-	Diversifying Social Activities – Charity Dodge Ball.
